  "prompt": "What shall I do with a mouse which freezes on the screen and stop responding?",
  "response": "If your mouse freezes and stops responding, try these steps:\n\n1. Basic troubleshooting:\n- Move the mouse to different USB ports\n- Check mouse cable for damage\n- Replace batteries if using a wireless mouse\n\n2. Software solutions:\n- Press Ctrl + Alt + Delete to open Task Manager\n- Check if the mouse driver is unresponsive\n- Restart the computer\n- Unplug and replug the mouse\n\n3. Advanced solutions:\n- Update mouse drivers\n- Check for system updates\n- Disable mouse acceleration\n- Try a different mouse\n- Run system diagnostics\n\n4. If using a laptop:\n- Check touchpad settings\n- Disable/enable touchpad\n- Restart touchpad driver\n\n5. If persistent issues:\n- Reinstall mouse drivers\n- Check for hardware problems\n- Consider professional repair or replacement\n\nChoose steps based on your specific situation and technical comfort level.",
